notes: We collected an Argentine ant colony fragment (hereafter “Saratoga”) from a residential  orchard in Saratoga, Santa Clara County, California, USA (N37º 15' 23.5; W122º 00'  55.2"). Genomic DNA was extracted and purified from a single queen pupa  (Saratoga) and sequenced using seven runs of 454 FLX Titanium sequencing.  Additional worker-derived genomic libraries were constructed and sequenced  on the 454 and Illumina platforms." This study also sequenced the mt genome but the results seem unpublished. (Smith et al. Draft genome of the globally widespread and  invasive Argentine ant (Linepithema humile).  (2011) PNAS. 108(14):5673-5678
